\pard\nowidctlpar\b0\par
\pard This is a release version 0.7.4 of Component Synthesis using Model-Integrated Computing ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dre.vanderbilt.edu/cosmic" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul CoSMIC}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) suite of tools. Currently CoSMIC tool suite consists of \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li720 o\tab Platform-Independent Component Modeling Language (PICML)\par
o\tab Component QoS Modeling Language (CQML)\par
o\tab DDS QoS Modeling Language (DQML)\par
o\tab Language for Embedded Query and Traversal (LEESA). \par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
\pard PICML is a Model-Integrated Computing ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.isis.vanderbilt.edu/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul MIC}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) based paradigm for modeling CORBA Component Model ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.omg.org/technology/documents/formal/components.htm" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul CCM}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 ) based applications, which use the latest Deployment and Configuration Specification {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.omg.org/cgi-bin/doc?ptc/2003-07-02" }}{\fldrslt{\cf1\ul (D&C)}}}\cf0\ulnone\f0\fs20 , for configuration and deployment. CQML allows PICML-based models to capture the higher level QoS design intent and helps generate QoS configuration metadata from annotated models. DQML allows modeling of large number QoS knobs provided by DDS. LEESA is a domain-specific embedded language (DSEL) in C++ that provides a succinct and expressive notation for writing object structure (model) traversal.\par
\par
This document lists the new features that are introduced in the latest version.\par
